{
  "texts": [
    "Whether we construe artificial intelligence as more instrument-like or more person-like has implications for how beliefs based on information retrieved from AI are justified (Duede, 2022).",
    "For present purposes, however, the most important point is that reliance on AI is at least a candidate for threatening epistemic autonomy.",
    "6 Deepfake Detection, Self-Trust, and Epistemic Autonomy",
    "In the previous section, I argued that relying on AI presents at least a potential threat to epistemic autonomy.",
    "In this section, I argue that reliance on ADDs, in particular, would in many cases compromise epistemic autonomy."
  ]
}